              <h3>Upsides:</h3>
              <p>
                Marisa's charge attack destroys spirts, but also causes them to explode as if they had been activated. This allows her to easily
                set off chain reactions in any situation without relying on her slow scope. It also allows her to easily destroy Lily White and
                boss attacks, which also means easier access to the special items they drop.
              </p>
              <p>
                Her special ability allows her to cast spells more often, and recover more gauge which allows her to chain level 2 attacks back to back
                in intense situations (thus keeping her screen mostly safe). This is also very useful during spell wars that often occur in the late
                game because her opponent will likely be drained before she is.
              </p>
              <p>
                Her high unfocused speed is great for macrododging and synergizes well with her laser, which can be swept across the screen. This also
                works well with level 1 invincibility frames, allowing her even better survivability.
              </p>
              <p>
                Her ex attacks, vertical lazers that spawn after being signalized for a few frames, can easily box the opponent towards one side of the screen,
                which means they'll have a harder time clearing more bullets with their own spells. They are also rather oppressive.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
